    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love that you kicked off that whole pickle homage with a link to the pickle that started it all for me, too.  As a kid, we would wrap up big juicy rueben sandwiches, crack open that big bottle of Pepsi and never, no never, would that rueben be unwrapped without the <>big,<> <>CRISP<> Clausen&#8217;s wedge right there.  </></>I&#8217;ve got a quick brine method for all the softer veggies that I came across a few years back on a first date &#8211; if you can believe that.  The cukes went from farmer&#8217;s market to washing machine to jars and a ten-minute water process in an insulated cooler filled with boiling water.  The sting of vinegar was still there in the air, but the house didn&#8217;t have to become a summer sauna&#8230;</p>
